@DOC_HEADER@
This is the prototype GridShib-CA that will
authenticate a user using Shibboleth, and then create and install a
short-lived Grid credential based on that authentication on the user's
local system.  This credential is suitable for use with Grid Tools
such as GT4.
<h2>Try it out</h2>
To use the GridShib CA you need to have
<a href="http://java.sun.com/products/javawebstart/download.jsp">
Java Web Start</a> installed on your system.
<p>
<a href="https://computer.ncsa.uiuc.edu/gridshib-ca-@PACKAGE_VERSION@/">Try out the latest stable version of the GridShib CA</a>
<p>
Please note that the GridShib-CA is not a well known CA, so you will
need to install the GridShib-CA certificate to actually use generated
credentials. You can find the GridShib-CA certificate (along with the signing
policy file) here: <a href="/downloads/gridshib-ca-cert.tar">gridshib-ca-cert.tar</a>. Please note
the GridShib-CA is not production, use of it's credentials for production
purposes is not recommended and is at your own risk.
<p>
